HEADWORD: Anthelion
<hw>Ant*hel"ion</hw> <pr>(?; 277, 106)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Anthelia</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>anti</ets> + Gr. <?/ sun.]</ety> <fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A halo
opposite the sun, consisting of a colored ring or rings around the
shadow of the spectator's own head, as projected on a cloud or on an
opposite fog bank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

